Objective
Predict whether an exoplanet is likely to be detected via the Radial Velocity method based on stellar and orbital properties.
This reframes astronomy as a resource-allocation & decision-support problem.

🔁 Input → Output
Input (X):
•	Stellar properties
(st_teff, st_mass, st_rad, st_met, st_logg)
•	Orbital parameters
(pl_orbper, pl_orbsmax, pl_orbeccen)
•	Planet physical properties
(pl_bmasse, pl_rade, pl_insol)
•	System metadata
(sy_dist, sy_vmag, sy_gaiamag)
Output (y):
•	Binary label:
is_radial_velocity_detectable
(1 = detected via Radial Velocity, 0 = other method)


Success Criteria
•	ROC-AUC ≥ 0.80 on untouched test set
•	Stable performance across stellar mass & distance segments
•	Feature importance aligns with astrophysics intuition
📌 No dataset touched yet.
